list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: an idea, feeling, or opinion about something or someone, especially one formed without conscious thought or on the basis of little evidence.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: his first impressions of Manchester were very positive
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Ấn tượng đầu tiên của anh ấy về Manchester rất tích cực

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: an imitation of a person or thing, especially one done to entertain.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: he did an impression of Frank Sinatra
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Ông đã tạo ấn tượng về Frank Sinatra

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: a mark impressed on a surface by something.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: the impression of his body on the leaves
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: ấn tượng về cơ thể của mình trên lá

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: the printing of a number of copies of a book, periodical, or picture for issue at one time.
